From cfa90431f316f59ab547db5b3df3f81350778c4f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hariharan Ramanathan <hramanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Sep 2025 12:14:39 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k: Gracefully handle invalid NSS in mcs
 update

Currently, in 11n mode, while updating stats, a WARN_ON is triggered if
the NSS value is not between 1 and 8.

Update the logic to conditionally set the MCS value only when NSS is
within the valid range, thereby avoiding unnecessary warnings and
handling invalid NSS gracefully.

Fixes: Ifdcf1dac12914294361ad3cee723143df11b42f4 : UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k:
Datapath stats changes for ath12k unified driver framework

Patch-Dependency:
130-10-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Add-WARN_ON-checks-for-nss-value.patch

Signed-off-by: Hariharan Ramanathan <hramanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c
index 70fae2c..db93e41 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_tx.c
@@ -1822,9 +1822,6 @@ ath12k_wifi7_dp_tx_update_txcompl(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *dp_pdev,
 		txrate.nss = arsta->peer_nss;
 	spin_unlock_bh(&dp->dp_lock);
 
-	WARN_ON_ONCE(txrate.nss < 1 ||
-             (txrate.nss > hweight32(dp_pdev->ar->pdev->cap.tx_chain_mask)));
-
 	switch (ts->pkt_type) {
 	case HAL_TX_RATE_STATS_PKT_TYPE_11A:
 	case HAL_TX_RATE_STATS_PKT_TYPE_11B:
@@ -1845,7 +1842,10 @@ ath12k_wifi7_dp_tx_update_txcompl(struct ath12k_pdev_dp *dp_pdev,
 			return;
 		}
 
-		if (txrate.nss != 0)
+		if (txrate.nss < 1 ||
+		    (txrate.nss > hweight32(dp_pdev->ar->pdev->cap.tx_chain_mask)))
+			ath12k_warn(ab, "Invalid nss value: %d", txrate.nss);
+		else
 			txrate.mcs = ts->mcs + 8 * (txrate.nss - 1);
 
 		txrate.flags = RATE_INFO_FLAGS_MCS;
-- 
